<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,721,2031]" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis box="[199,269,790,816]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Color.</emphasis>
Males (
<figureCitation box="[367,494,790,817]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5A–C</figureCitation>
). Body mainly black with some regions yellowish-brown. Vertex, pronotum, and mesonotum yellowish-brown with broad median longitudinal white stripe crossing these structures (
<figureCitation box="[1267,1357,825,852]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Forewing with corium mostly black with apex light brown and two small circular pale maculae in between corium and clavus, one at base and another near midlength of claval suture; clavus brown (
<figureCitation box="[1094,1185,894,921]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). Legs mostly yellow; metafemur black (
<figureCitation box="[359,483,929,956]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5B, C</figureCitation>
). Abdomen with tergite III with lateral white macula (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1229,929,956]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5A, C</figureCitation>
); each segment of abdomen with dorsal median pair of small and few conspicuous yellow maculae (
<figureCitation box="[1061,1151,963,990]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
); in lateral view, sternites with lateral white macula (
<figureCitation box="[450,541,998,1025]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,721,2031]" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis box="[199,515,1033,1059]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Structure. Head and thorax.</emphasis>
Vertex (
<figureCitation box="[611,699,1033,1060]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
) with anterior margin rounded; as long as basal width at midline; subequal to pronotum length at midline. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[687,773,1067,1094]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5B</figureCitation>
) without median carina; in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1231,1317,1067,1094]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
) each side with row of seven sensory pits bordering sublateral carina, four pits bordering frontogenal carina, and a pair of pits bordering fastigium (linking the other two rows providing a triangle-like arrangement—with two isolated pits within, aligned diagonally).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,721,2031]" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[326,415,1206,1233]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
) with six sensory pits bordering lateral margins of disc and a group of fiver inner ones at posterior half. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[465,552,1241,1268]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
) without median carina; region outerad of lateral carina with eight to nine sensory pits.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,721,2031]" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis box="[199,313,1310,1336]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Tergite III (
<figureCitation box="[451,539,1310,1337]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with pair of sensory pits. Tergite IV (
<figureCitation box="[1158,1247,1310,1337]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with pair of sensory pits followed by an isolated ventral pair. Tergite 
<collectionCode box="[934,954,1345,1371]" country="Canada" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:13946" name="Royal British Columbia Museum - Herbarium" pageId="7" pageNumber="114" type="Museum">V</collectionCode>
(
<figureCitation box="[970,1058,1345,1372]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with one row of three sensory pits followed by an isolated ventral pair. Tergite 
<collectionCode box="[844,874,1380,1406]" country="Norway" name="Mykotektet, National Veterinary Institute" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">VI</collectionCode>
(
<figureCitation box="[889,976,1379,1406]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with pair of sensory pits followed by an isolated ventral pair. Tergite VII (
<figureCitation box="[711,799,1414,1441]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5C</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with one row of three sensory pits followed by an isolated ventral pair. Tergite VIII, in lateral view, with pair of sensory pits.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,721,2031]" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis box="[199,390,1483,1509]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[503,592,1483,1510]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5D</figureCitation>
) with anterior margin concave; with posterior margin convex. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[160,248,1518,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5E</figureCitation>
) with tectiform structure bearing tectiductus; ventral support inverted Y-shaped. Gonostylus (
<figureCitation box="[1341,1427,1518,1545]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5F</figureCitation>
) hook-like; anterior portion pointed; caudal portion curved anterodorsally; dorsal margin follows almost straight with a rounded protuberance in between anterior and median third; ventral margin mostly rounded; median third longer than high, setose. Endosoma (
<figureCitation box="[562,683,1622,1649]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5G, H</figureCitation>
) enclosing almost all phallobase and aedeagus lengths laterally and ventrally; asymmetrical, with two different sides linked ventrally: one side is longer and with apex curved ventrally, comma-like; and other side is shorter and apically truncated, bearing sub-triangular expansion ventrally directed to the longest side of endosoma at aedeagus midlength (
<figureCitation box="[742,831,1726,1753]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5G</figureCitation>
). Phallobase membranous, shorter than endosoma; enclosing aedeagus half-length laterally and ventrally; slightly visible in lateral view, apically and dorsally. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[160,280,1795,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5G, H</figureCitation>
) opened dorsally; apically, narrowing and with pair of aedeagal hooks (
<figureCitation box="[1075,1163,1795,1822]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5H</figureCitation>
), both with same length, longer and thinner than aedeagus, and curved anterodorsally, reaching the base of phallus. Suspensorium V-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[160,250,1865,1892]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1787,1811]" captionTargetBox="[164,1426,322,1747]" captionTargetId="figure-65@8.[151,1437,308,1763]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Papagona papoosa Ball, 1935, male holotype (USNM): (A) Dorsal habitus; (B) ventral habitus; (C) lateral habitus; (D) Pygofer, lateral view; (E) connective, anterior view; (F) style, lateral view; (G–H) Phallus, dorsal view (G) and lateral view (H). Scale bar: A–C = 0.5 mm; D–H = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225563" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225563/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 5G</figureCitation>
). Anal tube as long as wide; posterior margin rounded; setose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,721,2031]" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,406,1899,1926]" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Taxonomic notes.</emphasis>
Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Ball, E. D." box="[526,654,1899,1926]" pageId="7" pageNumber="114" pagination="37 - 41" refId="ref7573" refString="Ball, E. D. (1935) Some new Issidae, with notes on others (Homoptera-Fulgoridae). Bulletin of the Brooklyn Entomological Society, 30, 37 - 41." type="journal article" year="1935">Ball (1935)</bibRefCitation>
states in the generic description that the vertex of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ball" authorityYear="1935" box="[1217,1332,1900,1925]" class="Insecta" family="Caliscelidae" genus="Papagona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1217,1332,1900,1925]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Papagona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is longer than pronotum length (see Introduction), in the 
<typeStatus box="[676,774,1934,1960]" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ball" authorityYear="1935" box="[809,931,1935,1960]" class="Insecta" family="Caliscelidae" genus="Papagona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="papoosa">
<emphasis box="[809,931,1935,1960]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">P. papoosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it appears only slightly longer than pronotum length (
<figureCitation box="[238,329,1969,1995]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1217,1241]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,737,1193]" captionTargetId="figure-318@3.[151,1436,737,1193]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Live specimens of Papagona dietrichi sp. nov.: (A) male specimen; (B) female specimen. Photographs by Dr. C. H. Dietrich." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5225553" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5225553/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). However, this could be an intraspecific variation or artefact the specimen position when photographed. See taxonomic notes of 
<taxonomicName authority="De Freitas &amp; Zahniser &amp; Takiya, 2021" authorityName="De Freitas &amp; Zahniser &amp; Takiya" authorityYear="2021" box="[524,647,2005,2031]" class="Insecta" family="Caliscelidae" genus="Papagona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dietrichi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[524,647,2005,2031]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">P. dietrichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[654,743,2005,2031]" pageId="7" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[654,743,2005,2031]" pageId="7" pageNumber="114" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
above for comparative notes.
</paragraph>
